21:13.047 --> 21:17.233
Your proudest accomplishments in relationship 
to A&M?

21:25.586 --> 21:28.170
Haskell, it's hard to identify one. Well, it can be 
plural.

21:36.224 --> 21:46.114
Among those that I was pleased with the outcome of 
were these.

21:52.860 --> 21:57.364
In the first several years development of the 
College of Liberal Arts,

22:02.153 --> 22:05.839
Science had broken out because science wanted its 
own identity.

22:09.405 --> 22:28.836
Liberal arts, when it achieved its separate 
identity, seemed to move forward rapidly,

22:09.405 --> 22:28.836
both in scholarship of faculty, I think, as well as 
enrollment of students.

22:31.820 --> 22:42.213
Another accomplishment that I was proud of was my 
chairmanship of the Coordinating Committee of

22:31.820 --> 22:42.213
the Century Council. I think that enabled me to 
have some inputs into the deliberations of that

22:43.374 --> 22:57.372
organization which moved A&M forward.

23:03.882 --> 23:10.471
Another would be the origination of the honors 
program at A&M.

23:15.978 --> 23:24.289
After the big change took place, co-eds admitted, 
military no longer required. One day, Dick

23:24.330 --> 23:33.602
Ballinger, a professor of English, visited with 
me and said, Dean Hubert, there's been a little

23:24.330 --> 23:33.602
talk in the English department. about the 
desirability of starting an honors section in

23:34.325 --> 23:39.131
English. We're getting some outstanding 
students, and we'd like to take them a little

23:39.611 --> 23:49.102
faster and further than our ordinary curriculum 
would. How would you react to our establishing an

23:50.164 --> 23:54.749
honors program in English?" I said, Dick, it's a 
great idea. why don't we do it for the college and

23:58.169 --> 24:05.178
ask other departments if they'd like to join in 
establishing honors programs. He said, fine. I

24:06.380 --> 24:11.226
said, well, will you be the faculty sponsor of an 
honors program? And he said, yes. And that took off

24:13.469 --> 24:17.875
and was a success, I think.

24:22.281 --> 24:27.788
In the College of Education, I would point to the 
accreditation by the college and every one of its

24:28.257 --> 24:37.687
teacher education programs by the National 
Council for the Accreditation of Teacher

24:28.257 --> 24:37.687
Education. It's most unusual on a first visit by 
this evaluation team from NCATE for that

24:38.428 --> 24:50.822
institution to be approved in every one of its 
offerings. from baccalaureate through the

24:50.920 --> 24:54.924
doctorate, and A&M was. And I think that's a case of 
where I simply happened to be there when it took

24:55.724 --> 25:02.991
place. We had a great faculty, and they were the key 
elements in that accomplishment. But it's one

25:11.619 --> 25:15.062
that I am quite proud of. In the chancellor's 
office, Haskell, again, hard to say. I thought my

25:21.228 --> 25:30.327
proposal for the reorganization of the system was 
sound in

25:21.228 --> 25:30.327
my single-track way, I guess, of thinking of 
things. I still think it was a good thing for the

25:34.231 --> 25:55.217
system, although I

25:34.231 --> 25:55.217
think it would take

25:34.231 --> 25:55.217
the Green Berets in full force armor to make it 
feasible again, politically feasible. Those are

25:56.547 --> 26:02.414
some of the things along the way. What's your 
favorite Aggie story? Got to be some moment you

26:08.962 --> 26:12.146
remember that you loved. Yes.

26:16.332 --> 26:20.417
My favorite Aggie story is this one. It's used as an 
illustration.

26:28.441 --> 26:35.934
during what I call the golden years of A&M, just how 
dramatically that institution turned around.

26:37.236 --> 26:54.685
From being recognized by high school students 
somewhere out there as a, as a cow college, on

26:37.236 --> 26:54.685
through up to becoming a full-fledged major 
university. And it's a story that goes like this.

27:01.303 --> 27:03.947
Education at A&M has changed dramatically. In 
fact, over the past 20 or 25 years, it has come full

27:05.068 --> 27:12.417
circle, 180 degree change. For example, at A&M 25 
years ago, all the Aggies were telling moron

27:14.560 --> 27:23.031
jokes. And today,

27:28.685 --> 27:30.007
That's my favorite story. If you mean an Aggie joke 
story, that's my favorite one. What

27:38.417 --> 27:57.882
advice would you give to the leaders of A&M today 
about what the role, I'll use the phrase role and

27:38.417 --> 27:57.882
scope, what advice would you give the leaders of 
A&M today, be they board members or

27:58.233 --> 28:03.518
administrators, the role and scope of Texas A&M 
University, what should it be?

28:09.544 --> 28:16.872
I would suggest to them that first they should 
study carefully the history of the university.

28:17.913 --> 28:26.822
Look at it from day one and over the past 100 and 
what, 10, 15 years now, I'm not sure, 114 years.

28:32.994 --> 28:41.589
Find out what brought it from its beginnings to 
where it is today. Know something about the

28:43.533 --> 28:49.924
essence of a land-grant college and the fact that 
The original premise behind a land-grant college

28:51.659 --> 29:20.805
hasn't been abandoned, but the change in the 
nature of our nation

28:51.659 --> 29:20.805
has taken us to the point where a

28:51.659 --> 29:20.805
true college-university type institution must 
go far beyond the emphasis upon agriculture and

29:21.967 --> 29:25.092
the mechanical arts. That would be my first 
recommendation

29:27.075 --> 29:39.793
for

29:27.075 --> 29:39.793
leaders of the university.

29:42.738 --> 29:46.303
I would suggest next that

29:51.413 --> 30:04.518
That they seek good advice if they are not attuned 
to the

29:51.413 --> 30:04.518
various components of a top university.

30:06.903 --> 30:13.135
Seek good advice and know what questions to ask of 
whom. Knowing which question to ask and to whom to

30:14.448 --> 30:34.212
address that question is exceedingly important 
for administrators, governing board members,

30:14.448 --> 30:34.212
faculty members, and all of us. I think those would 
be my two major recommendations. Know the

30:40.302 --> 30:44.489
history, seek good advice, and know what 
questions to ask. Okay, one light question and

30:45.670 --> 30:50.017
then two serious questions and we're finished. 
The light question is did any students or anybody

30:50.037 --> 31:03.658
else ever try to play any jokes or pranks on you as a 
teacher, as an administrator?

31:06.558 --> 31:08.821
Not that I recall. Nobody in class tried to set one 
up or anything? No. Okay. All right. Next to last

31:15.150 --> 31:16.252
question. Looking back, what effect has it had on 
your life that you came to Texas A&M in 1959?

31:28.209 --> 31:31.333
Well, it's had a...

31:33.220 --> 31:43.371
It's had a very dominant role in

31:33.220 --> 31:43.371
my life after A&M. It

31:45.273 --> 31:56.166
has brought me to a recognition that this 
community is an important community. This

31:56.766 --> 32:02.873
university is an important university.

32:07.004 --> 32:08.773
must not take the short view. They

32:08.813 --> 32:14.382
need to look well into the future.

